reviews.review_text: 10.1.80 Crystal clear SBD, but this was apparently a Rehearsal for the upcoming Radio City run leading up to Halloween Night.  If you love acoustic guitar you'll enjoy this.  But it is nothing like a live show.  Difficult to rate as a performance, because it wasn't one, but I will give 4 stars, because the voices of Jerry and Bob sound great, and the guitar work is masterful.  Sound quality is great, except the bass drum and tambourine sound a little too close.

beautiful i created an account just to review this.  after a long night with little sleep and a day at the office under the fluorescents, this concert is perfect.  i could listen to jack-a-roe over and over again.  makes me want to cry it's so beautiful. 

i'm so glad internet archive is here.  i listen to the dead every day at work.  a lifelong passion.
